            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1253.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>ground turmeric</strong>, <strong>garam masala</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>paprika </strong>and <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to a bowl</p><p>Add <strong>1 tbsp</strong> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> of the <strong>natural yoghurt</strong>, the <strong>juice</strong> of <strong>1/2</strong> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lemon</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and stir to combine – this is your <strong>tikka marinade</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1606328123443-x200.jpg",
